<BaseLayout title="About">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center pb-4">F1 Race Panel Team</h1>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-12">
    <Card title="Daniel Luna">
      <h3 class="title">Software Developer</h3>
      <p>
        A third year student at The University of Chicago studying Computer
        Science and Mathematics, he wanted to use his skills in order to display
        data about a sport he is passionate about. He has always liked the
        analytical side of sports and F1 Race Panel is inspired by other sites
        which are available for baseball, basketball, and football to name a
        few. This project allowed him to explore new technologies both front-end
        and back-end. This project is something he intends on working on for the
        foreseeable future.
      </p>
    </Card>
    <Card title="Ta'Naija Fair">
      <h3 class="title">Software Developer</h3>
      <p>
        From the nearby city of Milwaukee, Wisconsin, Ta'Naija is a member of
        UChicago's Class of 2026. With her love of programming, she is majoring
        in Computer Science and aspires to become a Software Engineer. While she
        is not an F1 enthusiast, she loves an opportunity to learn new things
        and work on cool projects.
      </p>
    </Card>
    <Card title="David Luna">
      <h3 class="title">Graphic Designer</h3>
      <p>
        A first year at Syracuse University studying accounting, he learned to
        do digital graphics in high school and still does it in his free time.
        He is an avit fan of F1 and thought that this project would allow him to
        express his passion for the sport in a unique and interesting way.
      </p>
    </Card>
